1. **Create Web GIS Application Using Google Map API, PHP and MySQL**

In this tutorial I am going to explain to you how to create simple web GIS application using Google Map API as map service and MySQL database to store our data and PHP programming language.

I am using XAMPP Web Server which consist of Apache web server and MySQL database server. You can use any web server that support a PHP.

1.
  1. 1. **Scenario:**

We are going to create a simple database for hotels which used to store the Name, Description, Phone, Email and Stars in addition to Longitude and Latitude to store the geographical coordinates of the hotel.

And the hotels data which include the longitude and latitude is projected on the google map in web page.

1.
  1. 2. **Create the Database:**

Open the XAMPP Control Panel and start the Apache web server and MySQL database server.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

And then open your web browser and in the address bar write [http://localhost/] and press enter. Click on **phpMyAdmin** link. **phpMyAdmin** is web based interface for MySQL database.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

To create new database click on Databases button.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

In the Database Name field write the database name and specify the database collection. In database name write [tourism] and in collection select [utf8-general-ci]. And then click on create button.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Once the database created the phpMyAdmin asking you to create table. In the create table form write [hotels] for the table name, for Number of Columns write [8]. And then click Go.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Now we have to specify the properties of eight columns. The columns are (ID, NAME, DESCRIPTION, PHONE, EMAIL, STARS, LONGITUDE, LATITUDE).

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

And then click save. The following screen explain the structure of the hotels table.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Click on the insert link to insert some data for testing purpose. insert the following information and click Go.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

We need to insert information for another hotel. You can insert the following data. And click on the Go button.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Now we have created our database and table for hotels information and we have inserted information about two hotels.

1.
  1. 3. **Create PHP Application to Display Hotels Information from MySQL:**

You can use any text editor software to write PHP codes. I am using Notepad++.

Create a new folder in XAMPP root directory (X:\xampp\htdocs\) and rename the new folder [hotelsmap]. And then open Notepad++ editor. From main menu change select language and change the language to PHP.

The mysqli\_connect(HOST, USERNAME, PASSWORD, DATABASE) command used to link your PHP application to MySQL Database. in nodepad++ type the following code.

&lt;?php

$con= **mysqli\_connect** (&quot;localhost&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;tourism&quot;)

    **or**** die**(&quot; Connection Error ! &quot;);

?&gt;

Save your file in the hotelsmap folder and name it getHotels.php. mysqli\_query(DATABASE\_LINK, SQL\_STATEMENT) is used to execute any SQL query in MySQL database.

&lt;?php

$con= **mysqli\_connect** (&quot;localhost&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;tourism&quot;)

    **or**** die**(&quot; Connection Error ! &quot;);

$query= **mysqli\_query** ($con,&quot;SELECT \* FROM hotels;&quot;);

?&gt;

We create an array to store the SQL query results. The following command is used to create array in PHP.

 $temp= **Array** ();

Mysqli\_fetch\_assoc(QUERY\_VARIABLE) is used to read query result data from MySQL database row by row, we will put it in while loop to read all query result rows. And store this rows in our temp array.

&lt;?php

$con= **mysqli\_connect** (&quot;localhost&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;tourism&quot;)

    **or**** die**(&quot; Connection Error ! &quot;);

$query= **mysqli\_query** ($con,&quot;SELECT \* FROM hotels;&quot;);

$temp= **Array** ();

**while** ($row= **mysqli\_fetch\_assoc** ($query)){

    $temp[]=$row;

}

?&gt;

Echo statement used to display text in the web page, and json\_encode is used to convert the query result array to JSON format.

&lt;?php

$con= **mysqli\_connect** (&quot;localhost&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;tourism&quot;)

    **or**** die**(&quot; Connection Error ! &quot;);

$query= **mysqli\_query** ($con,&quot;SELECT \* FROM hotels;&quot;);

$temp= **Array** ();

**while** ($row= **mysqli\_fetch\_assoc** ($query)){

    $temp[]=$row;

}

**echo**** json\_encode**($temp);

?&gt;

Now save your edits and open your web browser and in address bar type the following URL: [http://localhost/hotelsmap/getHotels.php](http://localhost/hotelsmap/getHotels.php).

    google.maps.event.addDomListener**(**map **,**&#39;click&#39; **,**** function****(**evt**){**

        **var** mark **=**** new **google.maps.Marker** ({ **map** : **map** , **position** : **pos** });**

            &#39;&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; name=&quot;LATITUDE&quot; value=&quot;&#39; **+** evt.latLng.lat**()****+ **&#39;&quot;&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&#39;** +**

            &#39;&lt;input type=&quot;button&quot; value=&quot; Save &quot; onclick=&quot;saveHotel();&quot;&gt;&lt;/form&gt;&#39;

        info.open**(**map **,** mark**);**

At the end of loadMap() function call the newHotel() function. And now we will create a new function to save the information in database. The $(&quot;#frm&quot;).serializeArray(); is used to set the form data as array of objects and we will use $.post(&#39;serverapplication&#39;, {data},handler) to sent the form data to the server side application in order to store it in MySQL database server.

Now we will create the exportHotels.php application to export our data into CSV format for farther analysis. From file menu in notepad++ click on new to create a new file and change the language to PHP. And write the following code.

&lt;?php

$con= **mysqli\_connect** (&quot;localhost&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;root&quot;,&quot;tourism&quot;) **or**** die**(&quot; Connection Error ! &quot;);

$query= **mysqli\_query** ($con,&quot;SELECT \* FROM hotels;&quot;);

$temp= **Array** ();

**while** ($row= **mysqli\_fetch\_assoc** ($query)){

    $temp[]=$row;

}

**header** (&#39;Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8; encoding=UTF-8&#39;);

**header** (&#39;Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=hotels.csv&#39;);

$output= **fopen** (&#39;php://output&#39;,&#39;w&#39;);

**fputcsv** ($output, **array** (&#39;ID&#39;,&#39;NAME&#39;,&#39;DESCRIPTION&#39;,&#39;PHONE&#39;,&#39;EMAIL&#39;,&#39;STARS&#39;,&#39;LONG&#39;,&#39;LAT&#39;));

**if** ( **count** ($temp)&gt;0){

    **foreach** ($temp **as** $row){

        **fputcsv** ($output,$row);

    }

}
